column18:
PART 1:



THINKING ABOUT YOUR "FUTURE SELF"



 



In Part 1, your job is to reflect on a role model. Specifically, we want you to think about your "future self" - who you recall being over the next few years. What does this phrase bring to mind?



Specifically: what do you think are the benefits to feeling connected to your future? When might it actually be good for you to "act like" your future self? If you brought to mind your future self as a role model for motivating yourself today, in what types of tasks would that help? What, exactly, is your future self good at?







So you get a fully formed image of your future self, please write 5-10 full sentences answering these questions. To successfully complete the HIT, you MUST write at least 5-10 sentences so we know you are actually engaged in this task.
